{
  "stem": "4284.2",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The-- talking about service was that when I was taken to Lodz, it was by coincident one week before my bar mitzvah.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Bar mitzvah, I had trained for secretly, not knowing where it would be held because synagogues and temples didn't exist, of course.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But every once in a while, just to uphold Jewish tradition, you would have it maybe in a-- I can't say home because we didn't have homes-- a facility where there was a large room and people, your family, would get together and you'd rush through the service.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Well, I didn't even have that.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Consequently, the holding of services, which did exist in the ghetto secretly and irregularly, and in different places because you were not allowed to congregate.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But they did have Jewish services.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They even sometimes had other activities like somebody would present some songs or whatever it is.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Culture was being maintained in a haphazard manner because the Germans were not personally present except during the day.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So at night you were just closed off so attempts were made, and if there was a shul, or anybody bar mitzvah'ed, they would do it in a big hurry.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But they did manage to have some services.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But burial services, no.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "There was no-- unless you know rabbi, there was no service.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "It was just done very quickly.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "My mother worked in a factory about 14 hours a day making the front plates to German boots.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "The military boots had metal plates that always made this intimidating sound when they marched.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And of course to make the boots last longer.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And she had to drill the holes in them.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "A major opportunity for her to get an extra ration of food.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
